The government is investing 40
million kwanzas ($416,000) to build water systems, fountains and
boreholes this year to help preserve provincial supplies, the
Angola Press Agency said, citing the Kwanza Norte water
department head Silvestre Domingos Zangui.  Water project sites include Kikiemba and Lucala, Angop
